						<summary>

						<p>On the <hi rend="italic">balipīṭha</hi> in front of Narasimha temple on the hill.</p>						

						<p>It states that the offerings made to Narasimha are partaken of by several gods and sages such as Bali, Vibhīshaṇa, Bhīshma, Kapila, Nārada, Arjuna, Prahlāda, Vāsu, Aṁbarisha Vāyusuta, Śiva, Vishvaksēna Śuka, Sanaka etc. In characters of 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
